extra-collections’s documentation!¶

Extra Collections¶

“extra-collections” (“extra” for short) is a python library that provides an intuitive pythonic implementation of the most common data structures used in most of the software projects in the market. Some of these data structures are simple such as Stack or Queue; and some are much more complicated such as SkipList or RedBlackTree.

The name of this pacakge was inspired by the collections python library which provides a pythonic implementation for some basic data structures. “extra” provides an additional set of data structures, hence the name… “extra-collections”.

Available Data Structures¶

In this release, you can find +20 data structures that can be categorized into two categories:

1. List-based Data Structures:¶

  • Linked List

  • Doubly Linked List

  • Circular Linked List

  • Stack

  • Queue

  • Deque

  • Priority Queue

  • Skip List

2. Tree-based Data Structures:¶

  • Tree

  • Binary Tree

  • Binary Search Tree (BST)

  • AVL Tree

  • Splay Tree

  • Red-Black Tree

  • Min Heap

  • Max Heap

  • Treap

  • Trie

  • Radix Trie

  • Suffix Trie

How to use the documentation¶

Documentation is available in two forms: docstrings provided with the code, and a loose standing reference guide, available from the NumPy homepage.
